I read a lot of threads, and there is a lot of confusion regarding the time complexity of the solution. Below is a recursive solution for the problem, and its time complexity is O(n). It is so because We are Doing a Constant amount of operations inside each function call. 

If you recall the Merge sort, where we do O(n) number of comparisons at each level, and the number of comparisons in each recursion is equal to the size of the lists, the recursion depth is O(logn); therefore, the time complexity is O(nlogn).

On the other hand, the Total number of recursive function calls here is O(n), and each call does a constant number of operations. 

