# Approach:-

1. We pick the middle element to make a root and create a root node
2. Take left side of middle array pass them recursively to get left sub tree
3. use right side element to get right sub tree
4. Connect these sub tree with root node and simply return root node
   -->**Inorder traversal of binary search tree outputs the value in sorted order**

# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    public TreeNode sortedArrayToBST(int[] nums) {
        return CreateBST(nums, 0, nums.length - 1);
    }

    private TreeNode CreateBST(int nums[], int left, int right) {
        if (left > right) return null;
        int m = (right + left) / 2;
        TreeNode root = new TreeNode(nums[m]);
        root.left = CreateBST(nums, left, m - 1);
        root.right = CreateBST(nums, m+ 1, right);
        return root;
    }
}
```

