Idea: 
1. Each TrieNode has a flag indicating whether it is the end of a word in the Trie, and a Map that associate characters to TrieNodes. 
2. Each path from root to a leaf is a key/word.

Given a trie ["abc", "abde", "worb", "xyz", "xyzb"], to delete a word 'word', there are 4 cases,
1. If 'word' doesn't share any node with other words, delete all nodes of 'word', e.g., deleting "worb".
2. If 'word' is a prefix of other words, mark its leaf node as 'not a word', e.g., deleting "xyz".
3. If other words are prefixes of 'word', delete all nodes that are not shared with other words, deleting "xyzb".
4. If 'word' is not a prefix of other words and no word is a prefix of 'word', but 'word' shares some nodes with other words, delete all nodes that aren't shared with other words, e.g., deleting "abde"/"abc".
![image](https://s3-lc-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/users/walkboy/image_1533263564.png)


Complexity - Time: O(n) for inset(), search(), startsWith() and delete() where n is word.length, Space: O(1)
