### Complexity analysis:
##### Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
> Let $$n$$ be the size of the word.
> In all the $$3$$ methods, we iterate over the word which takes $$O(3.n)$$ time.

##### Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
> For each character in the string, we are creating a TrieNode array of size $$26$$ (in `insert()` method). Assuming there are $$n$$ characters in our string, we end up consuming a space of $$O(26.n)$$ which can be boiled down to $$O(n)$$.
