# Trie

#### How to implement the trie data structure.
1. data - store the character.
2. child - store the child, that starts with particular character.
3. wordEnd - Number of word that end at that character.

**Searching/inserting in O(word length) time**
```java
class Trie {

	char data;
	// to store all the children
	Trie[] child;
	// number of word that end at this character.
	int wordEnd;

	public Trie() {
		this.data = '-';
		this.child = new Trie[26];
		this.wordEnd = 0;

	}

	public void insert(String word) {
		Trie cur = this;
		for (char ch : word.toCharArray()) {
			// if no child with character ch, create a new child.
			if (cur.child[ch - 'a'] == null) {
				Trie newChild = new Trie();
				newChild.data = ch;
				// assign the new child to the current node.
				cur.child[ch - 'a'] = newChild;
				// move to the child node.
				cur = newChild;
			} else {
				// if there is a child, then move to the child node
				cur = cur.child[ch - 'a'];
			}

		}
		// increment the number of word that end at the last character of word.
		cur.wordEnd += 1;

	}

	public boolean search(String word) {
		Trie cur = this;
		for (char ch : word.toCharArray()) {
			// if there is no child for character ch, then word doesn't exits.
			if (cur.child[ch - 'a'] == null) {
				return false;
			} else {
				// move to the child node.
				cur = cur.child[ch - 'a'];
			}
		}
		// if wordEnd is >=1 means one or more word end at current character.
		return cur.wordEnd != 0 ? true : false;
	}

	public boolean startsWith(String prefix) {
		Trie cur = this;
		for (char ch : prefix.toCharArray()) {
			// if there is no path for character ch, then prefix doesn't exists.
			if (cur.child[ch - 'a'] == null)
				return false;
			// if there is a path move to the next node.
			else
				cur = cur.child[ch - 'a'];
		}
		// if we are able to traverse all the character of prefix, then prefix exists.
		return true;
	}
}

```

